The FCT Primary Health Care Development Board (FCTPHCDB) yesterday began the Outbreak Response Round 1 to end on December 18, aimed at vaccinating children under 5 years against polio. The Acting Executive Secretary, FCT Primary Health Care Board (FCT-PHCB), Dr. Iwot Ndaeyo A., disclosed to reporters that the board has made available several doses of vaccines for the exercise. He said the exercise has house-to-house teams, special teams, senior supervisors, monitors and supervisors from the National Primary Health Care Agency (NPHCA). The Executive Secretary said the exercise, which is being carried out with support from World Health Organisation (WHO), is to encourage parents to allow two drops of oral polio vaccine be administered to children from 0-59 months old.